kerchief, they used to carry you know. Tie it on four knots on the top, and carry it. And he was swinging, and he went up - up Jervis Street, that was past our house, up Jervis Street, and - he was just turning along St Johns Street, to - right at top of 
t
he bank, as - see what was - there was another chap, and this other chap, he went one road and this other chap went another road. And all of a sudden he just got off the kerb - onto the road, and down, never - never saw him again. Fell down the pit shaft.
 And - it opened and he dropped. And he was whistling at the time, he was always whistling, when the role is }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11670890\charrsid15817332 called up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
