. Well there's some on 'em here they go church - they go the catholic church Sunday morning. They come home and they aren't in the house above half an hour, they've got the same clothes on, they put the boiler on - washer on, start washing. Then you'll he
ar the spin drier go. They put the spin drier on and then - Sunday afternoon, about four o'clock they start ironing. You can see 'em in front of the window doing it. I said, well if you call that true -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 Did your mother and father go to chapel with you?
