\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 Was it just the girls and father again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
Ah well the eldest one I mean - her used to - look after her when her was bad. But I mean - the last illness her had it was - her was in bed - three month - almost three month and - 'course we had to pack - her had to pack u
p altogether sewing then. And - her seemed as if her weren't proper - soft somehow, you know, silly - couldn't do nothing or didn't know - put any - give her anything, her'd say her hadn't had it half an hour after her hasn't had it, didn't know and her d
i
dn't know what her'd done with it nor nothing. Used to get a hat - and - when her got up, she'd put a white apron on, put her hat on, and - had got a big mop of hair - big bun her used to have, and put this hat on, elastic underneath the bun at the back, 
a
nd then her'd put a big black shawl as a - well me - granny - crocheted it I - crocheted it I think it is - great big black 'un, used to double it and chick it over her shoulders and - walk off out. Shan't be a minute. You're - perhaps - about ten minutes
 
or quarter of an hour after you won't see her, you go all round - all round the streets, you wouldn't find her. And then you - perhaps come walking in about a couple of - or three hours after. Where have you been? I've only been a walk round, only been su
c
h a place. I've been there after you and couldn't find you. Well I've only been there, I've been nowhere else. Who have you been talking to? Nobody. No, used to come so - you know - proper lost her memory altogether. Oh he said it was - one of them - dose
s
, it was with - staring - and - migraine, you know, like - dress - cutting 'em out and that that's what's it. Oh yes, he - he explained what it was, the doctor, Doctor Adler did. And he told us, he said he could nothing with it, only all - get her outside
 as much as you could but you mustn't - not herself. Had to go with her. And you know you couldn't, I mean you - there was things we'd got to do in the house and - you couldn't very well go everywhere with her, but we had to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 So your elder sister in fact gave up work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
Oh yes, her pack - packed in altogether. But - same as I say, her - her always wanted me for go with her, well there's many a day I couldn't go to school, I stayed home from school. I did. When her said her was going out it was f
ine, we'll have a walk. That meant you'd - no need think of going - I said, I'm going to school. Oh well, I'll go meself, I'll go meself then. Oh I used to get so - awfully ill tempered. Shout at you. All right, I'll stay at home but you tell dad I - you 
k
ept me at home. Oh it don't matter. So - of course I - sometimes I used to say to - think to meself, I used to say to girls, tell teacher I've got to go out with me mother. You know, and then they got - when I went up and told teacher about it - said, wel
l that's the only thing I could do, shall have to look after her 'cos if anything happened to her - we should be to blame for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 It sounds quite a responsibility for a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid199517\charrsid15817332 young girl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 Oh yes, yes. Yes by gum. Same as they said and - they tried all 
rods for get her away but - her wouldna go. Tried to get her - at Southport, was a home in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Southport{\*\xmlclose} or whether it was the \{BLANK\}
 they tried get her, but - her wouldn't go. You weren't going to tie her down. 'Course, same as Doctor Adler tells you we shou
ld have all that for put up with, her'd be like that for about three or four years. And perhaps in about seven years time she'd be as right as ninepence again. I say seven years is a nice time for wait isn't it. Oh we did have a time with her. I mean it's
 a time to re - as you can remember to think as - if you'd got to go through it yourself now. Oh yes, I couldna go - I couldna go through it. Not being on me own now, I couldn't if I was like that. I should have - I'd have to go in a home straight away.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 In a way she was fortunate that she'd got four daughters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
Yes. But I mean there wasn't - there isn't - there wasn't a homes then same as there is now. Bucknall hospital was only for fever. And then there was only North Stafford Infirmary.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 Fam
ilies were left to cope with far more situations in those days than they are now?
