\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 Oh I didn't 
- no, not - never bothered they didn't. Well mother didn't have time for go. Me father wouldn't bother with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
But did you see that there were some people perhaps who had one standard of living and other people who lived differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 Oh yes, I mean - and - same as I say there's some on 'em, they're in one }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid199517\charrsid15817332 another\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
 house, borrowing this and borrowing that. But - no, dad always says, we - we have to work for our own, he says, and we buy our own. He says, and other folks must do the same. No, he's - had his rules.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
So you would see your family as being perhaps in the middle that there were perhaps other families who weren't as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
Oh aye. The - oh he said like he said if you keep yourself and neither borrow nor lend, he says - they can't say nothing about you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
But if you'd have had to describe yourself as either a working class or a middle class family, how would you have described yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 Well - middle class I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 If you were middle class and we've t
alked about the things that your family felt important what would you have said was sort of usual in a working class family? Were these the kind of people who borrowed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
Well - I can't say, I mean they've always been - that one road I mean, you always
 had it from the beginning. As - we know what money we've got at the weekend, and it's divided out so much for everything he says and when you've paid your rent and - and coal, he says, you know you've got your shelter. But - same as I say, and then there
's - so much for shoes, we used to have a - a list, what he used to - what was to pay out. Then same as he said he knew what he'd got left then, when the - when - dad always used to pay out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 He was in charge of family finance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026153 AW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 Yes. Oh yes. Oh aye, clubs, coal and everything he used to see to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12523876 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3500148\charrsid15817332 
